        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 26 at 8:27PM EDT until June 26 at 9:15PM EDT by NWS State College PA</headline>
        <description>SVRCTP

The National Weather Service in State College PA has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Central Franklin County in south central Pennsylvania...
Northeastern Fulton County in south central Pennsylvania...
South central Huntingdon County in central Pennsylvania...

* Until 915 PM EDT.

* At 827 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Fort
Littleton, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
McConnellsburg, Waterfall, Fort Littleton, Fannettsburg, Three
Springs, and Shade Gap.

Radar has indicated rotation within this severe thunderstorm.
Although a tornado is not immediately likely, tornadoes can develop
quickly during severe thunderstorms.

This includes The Pennsylvania Turnpike from mile markers 175 to 188.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay inside a well built structure and keep away from windows.</instruction>
